<h3>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h3>
<p><strong>Q.</strong> What happens if a child answers a poll?<br>
<strong>A.</strong> Bound Round from time to time will set up polls on our website to learn user&nbsp;preferences. The information we receive does not contain any personal information. The information will be used to create a better site for kids&nbsp;to enjoy.</p>
<p><strong>Q.</strong> What happens if a child enters a competition?<br>
<strong>A.</strong> When a child enters a competition through Bound Round, they will be asked for their email address and contact information. Once Bound Round has appraised all entries, the parent of the winning entry will be contacted to confirm address details to mail out the prize. Bound Round will not award the prize if parental approval is not given.</p>
<p><strong>Q.</strong>&nbsp; How does Bound Round use personal information about children and what happens to it?<br>
<strong>A.</strong>&nbsp; The information users&nbsp;provide is only used to send out products and services requested by the user, to send out prizes in competitions and to communicate updates, offers or membership benefits from Bound Round.</p>
<p><strong>Q.</strong> Do you sell your information to third parties?<br>
<strong>A.</strong> No!</p>
<p><strong>Q.</strong> How will I know if you make changes to the privacy policy?<br>
<strong>A.</strong> If we decide to change the Bound Round Privacy Policy, we will post those changes in this section of our website and they will be included in the next release of a Bound Round app.</p>
